<title>USA: BEFORE THE BELL - Adobe firms on S&amp;P 500 add.</title>
<headline>BEFORE THE BELL - Adobe firms on S&amp;P 500 add.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The imminent addition of Adobe Systems Inc to the Standard &amp; Poor's 500 Index spurred interest in the stock in early third market trade Thursday, lifting the shares almost two points.</p>
<p>Ahead of the regular-market open, Adobe climbed 1-7/8 to 41, traders said, noting a company's shares often rise after inclusion in the S&amp;P 500 on buying by index-linked mutual funds.</p>
<p>Last night, S&amp;P said Adobe will replace Santa Fe Pacific Gold Corp after the close of trade May 5. Santa Fe is being acquired by S&amp;P 500-component Newmont Mining.</p>
